SIMPLE: picker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Picker
<hw>Pick"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Pick</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, picks, in
any sense, -- as, one who uses a pick; one who gathers; a thief; a pick;
a pickax; <as>as, a cotton <ex>picker</ex></as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Pickers</xex> and stealers.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A machine for picking fibrous
materials to pieces so as to loosen and separate the fiber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Weaving)</fld> <def>The piece in a loom which
strikes the end of the shuttle, and impels it through the
warp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Ordnance)</fld> <def>A priming wire for cleaning
the vent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pickerel</ent>⟦br⟧
